tasks.description:
Create Next.js error.tsx files for every route group under apps/web/app/(app)/. Each error.tsx follows the same pattern — it's a client component that uses the ErrorFallback component from @gilbertus/ui.

Template for each error.tsx:
```tsx
'use client';

import { ErrorFallback } from '@gilbertus/ui';

export default function ModuleError({
  error,
  reset,
}: {
  error: Error & { digest?: string };
  reset: () => void;
}) {
  return <ErrorFallback error={error} resetErrorBoundary={reset} moduleName="ModuleName" />;
}
```

Create error.tsx for these routes (replace ModuleName with Polish module name):
- `(app)/error.tsx` — moduleName='Aplikacja'
- `(app)/dashboard/error.tsx` — 'Dashboard'
- `(app)/chat/error.tsx` — 'Chat'
- `(app)/chat/[id]/error.tsx` — 'Rozmowa'
- `(app)/intelligence/error.tsx` — 'Wywiad'
- `(app)/people/error.tsx` — 'Osoby'
- `(app)/people/[slug]/error.tsx` — 'Profil osoby'
- `(app)/compliance/error.tsx` — 'Compliance'
- `(app)/market/error.tsx` — 'Rynek'
- `(app)/finance/error.tsx` — 'Finanse'
- `(app)/process/error.tsx` — 'Procesy'
- `(app)/decisions/error.tsx` — 'Decyzje'
- `(app)/documents/error.tsx` — 'Dokumenty'
- `(app)/calendar/error.tsx` — 'Kalendarz'
- `(app)/admin/error.tsx` — 'Administracja'
- `(app)/settings/error.tsx` — 'Ustawienia'

Total: 16 error.tsx files. All follow the exact same template, only moduleName differs.
